  <!-- SECTION 1 -->
  <h2 id="what-is-claude">What Is Claude AI?</h2>

  <p>Claude AI is an <strong>AI assistant</strong> — a smart software program you can have a real conversation with. You type a message, and Claude reads it, thinks about the best response, and writes back in natural, clear language. It feels a lot like texting a very knowledgeable friend who can help you with almost anything.</p>

  <p>Claude is built on a <strong>large language model (LLM)</strong> — the same kind of technology behind ChatGPT and Google Gemini. But Claude has its own personality, its own strengths, and its own unique approach. It's particularly known for being thoughtful, careful, and genuinely helpful — especially on complex topics that require nuance.</p>

  <p>Think of Claude as your personal AI assistant that can help you:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Write better</strong> — essays, emails, blog posts, cover letters, captions</li>
    <li><strong>Learn faster</strong> — explain any topic in simple terms, act as a tutor</li>
    <li><strong>Work smarter</strong> — summarise long documents, analyse data, plan projects</li>
    <li><strong>Code easier</strong> — write, debug, and explain code in any language</li>
    <li><strong>Think clearer</strong> — brainstorm ideas, get feedback, weigh pros and cons</li>
  </ul>

  <p>The name "Claude" comes from the Claude Shannon, the mathematician who founded information theory. Fitting for an AI that lives and breathes information.</p>

  <!-- SECTION 2 -->
  <h2 id="who-made-claude">Who Made Claude AI? Anthropic Explained</h2>

  <p>Claude was created by <strong>Anthropic</strong>, an AI safety company founded in 2021 and based in San Francisco. Anthropic was co-founded by <strong>Dario Amodei</strong> (CEO) and <strong>Daniela Amodei</strong> (President), along with several other researchers who previously worked at OpenAI — the company behind ChatGPT.</p>

  <div class="callout callout-blue">
    <div class="callout-icon-row">
      <div class="callout-icon-wrap">🏢</div>
      <div class="callout-body">
        <strong>About Anthropic</strong>
        <p>Anthropic was founded with a specific focus on AI safety — building AI systems that are helpful, harmless, and honest. This mission directly shapes how Claude is trained and how it behaves. Claude is designed to be straightforward, to admit uncertainty, and to avoid harmful outputs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>Anthropic has raised billions of dollars from investors including Google and Amazon, making it one of the most well-funded AI companies in the world. Claude is their flagship product — and it has gone through several generations of improvements, with each version getting significantly smarter and more capable.</p>

  <p>In 2026, the Claude family includes Claude Haiku (fast and lightweight), Claude Sonnet (balanced), and Claude Opus (most powerful). As a beginner, the free tier gives you access to Claude Sonnet — which is already remarkably capable for everyday use.</p>

  <!-- SECTION 3 -->
  <h2 id="how-it-works">How Does Claude AI Work for Beginners?</h2>

  <p>You don't need to understand the technical details to use Claude. But a simple mental model helps you get much better results. Here's how it works in plain English:</p>

  <div class="steps-grid">
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>You Type a Message</h4>
        <p>Open Claude at claude.ai, type your question, task, or request in the chat box — exactly like sending a WhatsApp message. You can ask in English, Hindi, or most other languages.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Claude Reads and Understands</h4>
        <p>Claude processes everything you wrote — the words, the context, the intent. It understands not just what you said but what you actually mean, including nuance and tone. This is what makes it feel so human.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Claude Thinks and Generates</h4>
        <p>Using its training on vast amounts of text, Claude reasons through the best possible response — checking for accuracy, weighing options, and structuring the answer clearly before it starts writing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">4</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>You Get a Clear, Helpful Reply</h4>
        <p>Claude writes back in natural language, structured for readability. You can then follow up, ask for changes, dig deeper, or start a completely new topic — all in the same conversation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">5</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>You Can Upload Files Too</h4>
        <p>On paid plans (and some free access), you can upload PDFs, Word documents, spreadsheets, and images. Claude reads them and answers your questions about the content — a game-changer for students and researchers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>One thing that makes Claude special is its <strong>very long context window</strong>. This means Claude can hold an enormous amount of information in a single conversation — reading entire books, long research papers, or huge chunks of code without forgetting the beginning. Most AI assistants struggle with long documents; Claude handles them naturally.</p>

